article.headline: Texas-Pan American 77, Texas-Permian Basin 65
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Zach Trader scored a game-high 22 points to lead Texas-Pan American to a 77-65 win over Texas-Permian Basin on Saturday in the season opener for both teams. Brian Burrell hit five 3-pointers and finished with 18 points and seven rebounds for the Broncs (1-0). Emmanuel Jones scored 12 points and Paul Stoll added 10 points and five assists. Robert Harris and Justin Bailey each scored 15 points for Texas-Permian Basin (0-1). But their team could not overcome its 20 turnovers, twice the number committed by Texas-Pan American. The Broncs sank 84 percent of their free throws, including all six from Trader. Overall, the team was 21-of-25 from the line. The Broncs jumped out to a 12-point first-half lead, which proved to be the difference in the game. The team's matched one another point for point after the break.
